{
  "stem": "16930.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 246.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I was a kid, I remember the kids calling me Jew boy, before-- before-- before Hitler came in.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we had-- we had-- they had classes, religious classes, or religious moments, whatever it was, in the school.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Jewish children went out during that period.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Another boy and myself went out of class, left the class during that period.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In this particular class, there were just two of us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this was not a-- a Jewish neighborhood specifically.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were Jewish neighborhoods in Vienna.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and kids used to call you Jew boy.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And sort of in a sense, you're a little bit-- I don't think they were beating up on me then, at that point, before Hitler came.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But they sort of-- you know, it made a difference known, particularly around Christmas, when all that hoopla, Christmas hoopla, which was much more than here in America.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The kids were dressed in red, like little devils or little red jumpers and things.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were skating on the streets and throwing snowballs.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so you got into more of a Christmas atmosphere in Vienna, more than over here.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In a sense, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In a sense, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well-- well, after Hitler came, of course, I was just-- and then when Hitler came in '38, I was barely nine years old.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So after Hitler came, the-- the children became more aggressive towards Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You could be beaten up in the street for being a Jew.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember trying to-- to stay in the adults that are walking to-- for protection.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And sometimes it would work.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And sometimes adults would pull away and wouldn't give a damn, would just let the other kids beat up on the Jewish children or assault the Jewish children, taunt and physically assault.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
